From: Wang Lian <lianux.mm@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 30 Mar 2026 12:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] mm: add vmstat counters to track page fault I/O retries

To evaluate the efficiency of the page fault retry mechanism, especially
under severe memory pressure and scheduling preemptions, it is crucial
to monitor the success rate of I/O retries.

When a major fault occurs, the kernel drops the lock and triggers I/O.
However, during the unlocked window, the newly fetched folio might be
evicted by LRU reclaim before the faulting thread can re-acquire the
lock and map it, leading to a wasted I/O wait.

This patch introduces two new vmstat counters:
- `retry_mmap_drop`: Incremented every time filemap_fault drops the
  lock and jumps to `out_retry`.
- `retry_io_miss`: Incremented when a fault is retried (FAULT_FLAG_TRIED)
  but no page is found in the page cache, indicating the folio was
  likely stolen.

These counters provide direct observability into the "retry hell"
phenomenon under memory thrashing.

Signed-off-by: Wang Lian <lianux.mm@gmail.com>
---
 include/linux/vm_event_item.h | 2 ++
 mm/filemap.c                  | 3 +++
 mm/vmstat.c                   | 2 ++
 3 files changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/include/linux/vm_event_item.h b/include/linux/vm_event_item.h
index 22a139f82d75..29f93695471d 100644
--- a/include/linux/vm_event_item.h
+++ b/include/linux/vm_event_item.h
@@ -37,6 +37,8 @@ enum vm_event_item { PGPGIN, PGPGOUT, PSWPIN, PSWPOUT,
 		FOR_ALL_ZONES(PGSCAN_SKIP)
 		PGFREE, PGACTIVATE, PGDEACTIVATE, PGLAZYFREE,
 		PGFAULT, PGMAJFAULT,
+		RETRY_MMAP_DROP,
+		RETRY_IO_MISS,
 		PGLAZYFREED,
 		PGREFILL,
 		PGREUSE,
diff --git a/mm/filemap.c b/mm/filemap.c
index 406cef06b684..4fd0f2993775 100644
--- a/mm/filemap.c
+++ b/mm/filemap.c
@@ -3550,6 +3550,8 @@ vm_fault_t filemap_fault(struct vm_fault *vmf)
 		/* No page in the page cache at all */
 		count_vm_event(PGMAJFAULT);
 		count_memcg_event_mm(vmf->vma->vm_mm, PGMAJFAULT);
+		if (vmf->flags & FAULT_FLAG_TRIED)
+			count_vm_event(RETRY_IO_MISS);
 		ret = VM_FAULT_MAJOR;
 		fpin = do_sync_mmap_readahead(vmf);
 retry_find:
@@ -3660,6 +3662,7 @@ vm_fault_t filemap_fault(struct vm_fault *vmf)
 	 * re-find the vma and come back and find our hopefully still populated
 	 * page.
 	 */
+	count_vm_event(RETRY_MMAP_DROP);
 	if (!IS_ERR(folio))
 		folio_put(folio);
 	if (mapping_locked)
diff --git a/mm/vmstat.c b/mm/vmstat.c
index 86b14b0f77b5..c4475873deb4 100644
--- a/mm/vmstat.c
+++ b/mm/vmstat.c
@@ -1316,6 +1316,8 @@ const char * const vmstat_text[] = {
 
 	[I(PGFAULT)]				= "pgfault",
 	[I(PGMAJFAULT)]				= "pgmajfault",
+	[I(RETRY_MMAP_DROP)]			= "retry_mmap_drop",
+	[I(RETRY_IO_MISS)]			= "retry_io_miss",
 	[I(PGLAZYFREED)]			= "pglazyfreed",
 
 	[I(PGREFILL)]				= "pgrefill",
